# emoji-react ‚Äî a tiny key‚Üíglyph table read back by name in a template.
#
# `map name glyph` records `context.icon[name]`; `react name n` reads the
# glyph with `${context.icon[name]}` and repeats it. The whole feature is
# one dynamic map read ‚Äî the reaction line just names a key the table
# already holds.
extension react
context
    icon {}
end
function map
    arg literal "map"
    arg capture name ident
    arg capture glyph ident
    set context.icon[name] glyph
end
function react
    arg literal "react"
    arg capture name ident
    arg capture who tail
    write `${who} reacted ${context.icon[name]}
`
end
